Diagnosis.
Vertical process of gonopod strongly sclerotized along margin or lateral margins (
Fig. 20B, D
); paramere sometimes dilated distally (
Fig. 20A
); aedeagal median rod sometimes with 1 small acute projection (as fig. 
17 in
Toda & Peng 1990
); basal bridge of aedeagal median rod strongly sclerotized, apically with 1 sometimes bifurcated process per side (
Fig. 20B, D
).
